A vast curved planet Earth viewed from space at the terminator line where day meets night, with multiple antique pocket watches and modern digital clocks floating in orbit around it, each displaying different times. The clocks cast long shadows across the planet's surface, their hands frozen at various hours. Golden sunlight streams from the left side while deep blue twilight engulfs the right. The watches range from ornate Victorian brass timepieces to sleek contemporary designs, all suspended weightlessly against a star-filled cosmic backdrop. Vintage style with warm sepia tones blending into cool midnight blues, reminiscent of 1920s travel posters with rich textures and slightly faded edges.
